# Aivora — One AI Agent to Organize Your Entire Life

Aivora is an autonomous personal life manager and concierge powered by **Google ADK 2.0**, **FastAPI**, **Next.js 15 (App Router)**, and **Model Context Protocol (MCP)**.

## Architecture & Technology Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15, React 19, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, TypeScript.
- **Backend**: Python 3.13, FastAPI, asynchronous SQLAlchemy (`aiosqlite`/`aiomysql`), Pydantic v2.
- **AI / Agent Framework**: Google ADK 2.0 Coordinator Workflow with specialized task-mode sub-agents:
  - Travel Planner Agent
  - Weather Forecast Agent
  - Budget Estimator Agent
  - Packing Checklist Agent
  - Scheduler Agent (with Human-In-The-Loop gatekeeper cards)
  - Storage & Artifact Generator Agent
- **Tooling & Integrations**: Model Context Protocol (MCP) wrappers for external API calls (Google Calendar, Weather APIs).

---

## Quick Start (Local Development)

### 1. Backend Setup (FastAPI & ADK)
Ensure you have `uv` or Python 3.13 installed.

```bash
# Clone repository and navigate to root
cd Aivora

# Copy example environment configuration
cp .env.example .env

# Create virtual environment and install dependencies
uv venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
uv pip install -r pyproject.toml --all-extras

# Run tests
pytest tests/

# Start FastAPI development server on port 8000
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```
Backend Swagger API docs will be available at: `http://localhost:8000/docs`.

### 2. Frontend Setup (Next.js)
In a separate terminal:

```bash
cd frontend

# Copy local environment configuration
cp .env.local.example .env.local  # Default: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run linting check
npm run lint

# Start Next.js dev server on port 3000
npm run dev
```
Open your browser at `http://localhost:3000` to interact with the Aivora landing page and authentication UI.

